Subject: Marin Dri Award 
To: Quentina
Content:
The Marin Dri Award is granted by Ministry of Culture of Croatia since 1991. Its goal is to stimulate dramatic and theatrical work. Traditionally, award ceremony is held in Split at opening day of Maruli days. Prize includes fee and bronze sculpture made by Damir Matui.[1] [2][3][4][5]
